AER 1598707 is a spontaneous case, received on 24/Jun/2015 from a physician via BfArM (Germany : reference 
number: DEDCGMA15166542) and concerns a 73 year old male who developed neurologic neglect syndrome, 
progressive multifocal leukoencephalopathy, visual field defect, JC virus positive liquor (jc virus test positive), 
creatine kinase increased, watery diarrhea, suspected aspiration pneumonia, acute renal insufficiency, fall, ankle 
injury, suspected formation of antibodies against platelets whilst being treated with rituximab (Mabthera), idelalisib 
(Zydelig).
The patient's medical history included alcohol abuse, chronic lymphocytic leukaemia, aplasia, thrombocytopenia, 
chronic pancreatitis, glaucoma, chronic renal insufficiency, appendectomy, cholecystectomy, retinal detachment, 
vertebral fractures. Past drugs included fludarabine. Concomitant medications included bendamustine, globulin, 
immune (Immunoglobulin), aspirin, simvastatin. No concurrent conditions were reported
Since 1999, the patient was diagnosed with (Stage Binet C / RAI stage 4) chronic lymphocytic leukaemia.  On an 
unspecified date in /Oct/2013, the patient started therapy with intravenous rituximab (dose, form, frequency not 
reported) for chronic lymphocytic leukaemia progression. Later, this therapy was stopped in /Mar/2014 and was 
restarted on 26/Nov/2014 with oral idelalisib 100 mg (frequency, form not reported) for chronic lymphocytic 
leukaemia progression. Approximately since 15/May/2015 he suffered from visual field loss on the left side, neglect 
on the left side and leg paresis on the left side. On (b) (6)  he developed neurologic neglect syndrome. On 
(b) (6)  due to increased uncertain gait he fell down, injured his right ankle and presented at hospital. Cranial 
computed tomography performed on (b) (6)  revealed fresh medullary ischemia in the parieto-occipital region 
on the right side. Sub-acute cerebral ischemia was suspected. Rituximab and idelalisib were discontinued on the 
same day. Same day urea was 58 mg/dL (17-43), creatinine was 1.6 mg/dL, uric acid was 8.7 mg/dL, total protein 
was 54 g/L (64-83), glomerular filtration rate was 43 mL/min, potassium was 2.9 mmol/L (3.5-5), calcium was 1.93 
