The physician assessed neurologic neglect syndrome, progressive multifocal leukoencephalopathy, visual field 
defect and JC virus positive liquor as medically significant.
The physician did not provide a causality of neurologic neglect syndrome, progressive multifocal 
leukoencephalopathy, visual field defect, JC virus positive liquor (JC virus test positive), creatine kinase increased, 
watery diarrhea, suspected aspiration pneumonia, acute renal insufficiency, fall, ankle injury, suspected formation 
of antibodies against platelets with rituximab and idelalisib.
No further information was provided.
This confirmed case of progressive multifocal leukoencephalopathy (PML) is being expedited per 
Roche/Genentech Enhanced Pharmacovigilance Plan for PML
Additional information was received on 02/Jul/2015, following information was added to the case : Source 
identification number of health authority DEPEIPEI2015038780 was added, new reporter was added, patient details
updated (initials and date of birth, previously not reported), event description was updated.
Additional information was received on 23/Nov/2015, following information was added to the case: Medical history 
except alcohol abuse, past drugs: fludarabine, concomitants, rituximab additional regimen, dose of idelalisib was 
corrected from 1000 mg to 100 mg, new events: creatine kinase increased, watery diarrhea, suspected aspiration 
pneumonia, acute renal insufficiency, fall, ankle injury, suspected formation of antibodies against platelets and 
laboratory tests.